---
import Layout from '../../../layouts/Layout.astro'
---

<Layout title="Install & Overview - Preact">
  <div class="mb-4 text-sm font-mono text-neutral-500 uppercase tracking-widest">
    @elekcsv/preact
  </div>

  <h1 class="mb-8 border-b-2 border-black pb-4">5.1 Install & Overview</h1>

  <p class="text-xl text-neutral-600 leading-relaxed mb-10">
    The <code>@elekcsv/preact</code> package provides the <code>useCSVImporter</code>
    hook for lightweight, reactive CSV imports in Preact apps. It wraps
    <code>@elekcsv/core</code> and exposes a step-based state machine plus helper
    methods for mapping and validation.
  </p>

  <h2>Installation</h2>
  <p>
    Install the Preact package with the core engine, then wire the hook into your
    own uploader UI.
  </p>

  <pre><code>npm install @elekcsv/preact @elekcsv/core
# or
yarn add @elekcsv/preact @elekcsv/core
# or
pnpm add @elekcsv/preact @elekcsv/core</code></pre>

  <h2>Why the Preact Hook?</h2>

  <ul>
    <li>
      <strong class="text-black">Small Runtime, Full Control:</strong> Keep bundle
      size low with Preact while still using the full elekcsv parsing and
      validation pipeline.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong class="text-black">Step-Based Flow:</strong> React to import stages
      like <code>parsing</code>, <code>mapping</code>, <code>review</code>, and
      <code>complete</code> without building your own wizard logic.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong class="text-black">Headless by Design:</strong> Bring your own dropzone,
      table, and error UI while the hook handles mapping, validation, and state
      transitions.
    </li>
  </ul>

  <div class="mt-16 flex justify-end">
    <a
      href="/docs/preact/basic"
      class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-6 py-3 bg-black text-white rounded-md text-sm font-medium hover:bg-neutral-800 no-underline! transition-colors"
      style="text-decoration:none;"
    >
      Next: Basic Usage
      <svg class="w-4 h-4" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"
        ><path
          stroke-linecap="round"
          stroke-linejoin="round"
          stroke-width="2"
          d="M14 5l7 7m0 0l-7 7m7-7H3"></path>
      </svg>
    </a>
  </div>
</Layout>
